    <h2><a href="/how-to-wear-leggings" class="title">Wear Leggings Without Looking Like A Coed</a></h2>
    <p class="byline">

      By 
    
    <a href="/author/connie-wang" rel="author"><span itemprop="author">Connie Wang</span></a>
    
      
      
    </p>

    <div class="body">A few years after the reappearance of leggings on the runway, wearing them in public is <em>still</em> a hotly debated topic. However, we think that the majority of the evidence provided by the anti-leggings constituency has to do with the whole North Face fleece + running shoe + leggings phenomenon, a post-workout look that's way too popular among the college set, that we see way too often at our neighborhood bars.<p></p> 

If you steer clear of that combo, you'll find quite a few chic ways to wear leggings that <em>won't</em> call to mind the wait for the elliptical. Ahead, we present nine ways to rock a pair of leggings — without looking like a coed.</div>

                <div class="long-asset vert">
        <a href="/how-to-wear-leggings">
                      <img src="http://static1.refinery29.com/bin/entry/efd/333x500b/164291/to-achieve-that-sporty-chic-look-asos.jpg" alt="to-achieve-that-sporty-chic-look-asos"    />
          
        </a>
        <a href="/how-to-wear-leggings"><div class="slideshow-ribbon lg"></div></a>
      </div>
      
    

