    <h2><a href="/bustier-top-styling-guide" class="title">Trendy, Not Trampy: 6 Chic Ways To Wear A Bustier Top</a></h2>
    <p class="byline">

      By 
    
    <a href="/author/holly-e-thomas" rel="author"><span itemprop="author">Holly E. Thomas</span></a>
    
      
      
    </p>

    <div class="body">We know what you're thinking: <strong>Bustier tops</strong> have a certain boudoir feeling that can be extra-tricky to navigate. While wearing one out of the house entails a certain amount of risk — no one wants to be nicknamed the Merry Widow of Washington, after all — we love a good style challenge, and we're game for this one. So, we're going to show you <strong>how to make this lingerie-model staple look chic and sophisticated</strong> enough that you can wear it everywhere. And we mean <em>everywhere</em> — to work, on weekend errands, to dinner, and out on the town. We promise these looks are ladylike and lovely (and not the least bit trampy) — click through to see for yourself.</div>

